cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on the overfitting of deep generative networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with image generation and analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GANs, which are a popular type of deep learning model used in image generation, and this could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of off-the-shelf GAN generators for face inpainting and super-resolution, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
